President Obama expressed his sadness over the passing of Carlos Hernandez Gomez, a political reporter from Chicago. The President described Carlos as a dedicated reporter who was committed to telling the truth about Chicago. He also mentioned that Carlos was known for asking hard questions but always played it straight. President Obama considered Carlos a role model and enjoyed their interactions during his time as a State Senator and on the campaign trail. The President extended his thoughts and prayers to Carlos' wife Randi and his family.